ABUJA – The Senate has appointed Senator Abba Moro as Chairman of the Committee on Federal Character and Inter-Governmental Affairs. President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, made the announcement moments before the Senate adjourned the plenary on Wednesday. Abba Moro replaces the former Chairman, Senator Danjuma La’ah (Kaduna South), who was nominated by the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) as the new Deputy Minority Whip of the Senate. -Advertisement- The PDP had in a letter to the Senate President announced the nomination of Senator La’ah to replace Senator Ibrahim Danbaba cross-carpeted to All Progressives Congress (APC). While announcing Senator Moro’s appointment, Senator Lawan explained that “the new Chairman of the Committee on Federal Character and Inter-Governmental Affairs is Senator Abba Patrick Moro representing Benue South. “We wish him a good tenure even though we have only just about a year to go.”